---
import ShellLayout from '@layouts/app.astro';
import ViewFrame from '@layouts/frame.astro';
---

<ShellLayout>
	<ViewFrame>
		<div data-is='layer' data-variant='under'>
			<figure data-is='background'>
				<img
					src='https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1697538022268-c565529e616f?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D'
					alt='Mass timber architecture background'
				/>
			</figure>
			<span
				data-is='background'
				style='background-color: hsl(from var(--clr-background__lowered) h s l / 75%); backdrop-filter: blur(0.5ex);'>
			</span>
		</div>

		<nav style='place-content: space-between; place-items: center;'>
			<button data-variant='outline'>
				<i data-is='icon'> menu </i>
			</button>

			<h6
				style="font-family: 'Oi'; text-align: center; text-box: trim-both cap alphabetic; white-space: nowrap;">
				TinkXo
			</h6>

			<a
				href={'#' + crypto.randomUUID()}
				data-is='button'
				data-variant='outline'>
				<i data-is='icon'> phone </i>
			</a>
		</nav>

		<p style='font-size: var(--nm);'>
			TinkXo ignites a NEW ERA where<br />we don’t just build — we *cultivate*.
		</p>

		<x-row
			style='border-bottom: solid 1px var(--clr-text__base); flex: 1 0 max-content; padding-block: var(--nm); place-content: space-between; place-items: end;'>
			<span
				style='float: right; flex-shrink: 1; min-width: 0; text-box: trim-both cap alphabetic;'>
				SCROLL
			</span>
			<h1 style="font-family: 'Oi'; text-box: trim-both cap alphabetic;">
				AMENITIES
			</h1>
		</x-row>

		<p style='font-size: var(--nm); place-self: end; text-align: right;'>
			Timber is more than a material—it’s<br />
			a cornerstone for a thriving, regenerative<br />
			future in which built spaces breathe and evolve.
		</p>

		<x-grid style='--gap: var(--nm); --cols: 2;'>
			<div></div>
			<div></div>

			<x-group style='gap: var(--nm);'>
				<p>
					At TinkXo, we believe buildings should be more like forests—alive,
					adaptive, and symbiotic with the world around them. As climate change
					intensifies, rethinking our spaces is no longer optional. It’s urgent.
				</p>
				<p>
					Mass timber is our medium of transformation. Naturally
					carbon-negative, it sequesters{' '}
					<span>CO<sub>2</sub></span> as it grows and continues to store it for decades,
					turning each structure into a living climate ally.
				</p>
			</x-group>

			<x-group style='gap: var(--nm);'>
				<p>
					TinkXo doesn’t just design buildings—we plant ideas. We’re cultivating
					hubs where people connect, businesses bloom, and nature finds its
					place again in our urban fabric.
				</p>
				<p>
					From scent and touch to temperature and texture, timber is not just
					sustainable—it’s sensorial. It's architecture that speaks to the body,
					the soul, and the future.
				</p>

				<a href={'#' + crypto.randomUUID()}>
					<span>Enquire Now</span>
					<i data-is='icon'> arrow_right_alt </i>
				</a>
			</x-group>
		</x-grid>

		<style lang='css' is:inline>
			@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oi&family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,100;0,200;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;0,900;1,100;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800;1,900&display=swap');

			@scope {
				:scope {
					display: flex;
					flex-direction: column;
					font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
					gap: var(--xl);
					overflow: auto;
					padding: var(--sm);
				}
			}
		</style>
	</ViewFrame>
</ShellLayout>
